  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "1 Peter 3:17-18",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Peter 3:17-18",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "For it is ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "infinitely ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "better, if the will of God be so ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— That you should suffer; and his permissive will in this respect appears from his providence; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "that ye suffer for well-doing, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "rather ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "than for evil-doing ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— The testimony of a good conscience, and the sense of the divine favour, affording the no blest supports in the former case; whereas, in the latter, the severest torments that can be endured are those which the guilty mind inflicts upon itself; to which may be added, that while we suffer for the truth, we have the comfort of reflecting that we follow our blessed Redeemer, which is another most powerful source of consolation. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "For Christ also hath once suffered for sins ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Not his own, but for ours, to make an atonement for them; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the just for the unjust ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Or the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "holy for the unholy; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for the word ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "just ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "here denotes a person who has fulfilled not barely social duties, but every branch of righteousness; and the word ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "unjust ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "signifies not only those who have wronged their neighbours, but those who have transgressed any of the commands of God; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "that he might bring us to God ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Might reconcile God to us, and us to God; and might obtain for us his gracious favour here, his Holy Spirit, to renew us after his image, and might bring us to his blissful presence hereafter; by the same steps of suffering and of glory. It is justly observed by Macknight, that in the sufferings of Christ we have a clear proof that sufferings are no evidence of the wickedness of the sufferer, nor of the badness of the cause for which he suffers; and that the power of God, visible in Christ’s resurrection, affords to all, who lose their lives for the gospel, a sure ground of consolation and hope that God will raise them up at the last day. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Being put to death in the flesh ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— In the human nature; or in respect of that frail, mortal life he had on earth; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "but quickened ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Ζωοποιηθεις",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "made alive; by the Spirit ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— The Spirit of God and of Christ. “As Christ was conceived in the womb of his mother by the Holy Spirit, (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 1:35",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ",) so he was raised from the dead by the same Spirit; on which account he is said (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Timothy 3:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") to have been justified by the Spirit; and (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 9:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") to have offered himself without spot to God, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "through the eternal Spirit. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "It is true the resurrection of Christ is ascribed to the Father, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Corinthians 6:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Corinthians 4:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ephesians 1:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; but that is not inconsistent with Peter’s affirmation in this verse;” for the Father may, with the strictest propriety, be said to have done what his Spirit did, especially as it was done to show that God acknowledged Jesus to be his Son. And our Lord’s words, (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 2:19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ",) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Destroy this temple, and in three days I will raise it up, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "are to be understood in the same manner. He raised it up by that Spirit which proceeded from him as well as from the Father.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
